-- China’s Shanghai Composite Extends Drop as Export Growth Slows
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-04-10T03:06:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/china-s-shanghai-composite-extends-drop-as-export-growth-slows.html
China’s stocks extended losses
after government data showed export growth halved in March.  The Shanghai Composite Index lost 0.9 percent to 2,266.02
att 11:04 a.m. local time. March exports increased 8.9 percent
from the previous year, compared with the previous month’s 18.4
percent growth.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
